issue.body:
I'm having quite some issues with `glfwGetKeyName`.
My keyboard layout is QWERTZ, the country Germany and the language German.
```c
#include <GLFW/glfw3.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
#include <stdio.h>

void key_callback(GLFWwindow* window, int key, int scancode, int action, int mods)
{
    printf("Key: %i, Scancode: %i\n", key, scancode);
    printf("glfwGetKeyName: %s\n\n", glfwGetKeyName(key, scancode));
}

int main()
{
    GLFWwindow* window;

    /* Initialize the library */
    if (!glfwInit())
        return -1;

    /* Create a windowed mode window */
    window = glfwCreateWindow(640, 480, "Hello World", NULL, NULL);
    if (!window)
    {
        glfwTerminate();
        return -1;
    }

    /* Register a callback */
    glfwSetKeyCallback(window, key_callback);

    /* Loop until the user closes the window */
    while (!glfwWindowShouldClose(window))
    {
        /* Poll for and process events */
        glfwPollEvents();
    }

    glfwTerminate();
    return 0;
}
```

Here's a list of keyboard keys on my keyboard (no caps lock) and their output of the above program, all of the outputs are incorrect:

* <kbd>-</kbd>
  ```
  Key: 47, Scancode: 61
  glfwGetKeyName: /
  ```

* <kbd></kbd>
  ```
  Key: 45, Scancode: 20
  glfwGetKeyName: -
  ```

* <kbd>`</kbd>
  ```
  Key: 61, Scancode: 21
  glfwGetKeyName: 
  ```

* <kbd></kbd>
  ```
  Key: 39, Scancode: 48
  glfwGetKeyName: 
  ```

* <kbd></kbd>
  ```
  Key: 59, Scancode: 47
  glfwGetKeyName: 
  ```

* <kbd></kbd>
  ```
  Key: 91, Scancode: 34
  glfwGetKeyName: 
  ```

All other key outputs are correct or are `null`.

The terminal I'm using (MobaXterm) is able to display all of these characters when I type them in the terminal.

Operating system: Windows 10, 64-bit
GLFW version string: 3.2.1 X11 GLX EGL clock_gettime /dev/js Xf86vm shared
I'm using the Windows Subsystem for Linux.

Can anyone else reproduce this?
